<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-05-09T05:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-05-09T05:00:00-05:00" n="103" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d103">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 808.00/1651.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Chargé
                                    d’Affaires</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-05-09T18:00:00+08:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">May 9, 1913—6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Both Houses have passed resolutions expressing appreciation, to be
                            communicated to you through the Chinese Minister at Washington.</p>
                        <p>In celebration of the recognition of the Republic by the United States,
                            deputations from commercial and other organizations and pupils and
                            teachers from the principal schools paraded with American and Chinese
                            flags and called at the Legation yesterday. They requested me to convey
                            to the Government and people of the United States their sincere
                            gratitude for its friendly action.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Williams</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>